{
    "thought_on_cooking_style": "The cooking style presented in the given recipes is very homey and approachable, with a focus on simple techniques that bring out the flavors of the ingredients. The steps are clearly described and easy to follow, making them suitable for cooks of various skill levels. The use of fresh ingredients and the combination of sauting, boiling, and baking techniques reflect a traditional and rustic approach to cooking that emphasizes comfort and taste.",
    "thought_on_recipe": "For the chicken pasta with peas recipe, we will follow a similar approach to the given examples, focusing on simple and clear steps that highlight the ingredients' natural flavors. The recipe will involve cooking pasta, sauting chicken, and combining it with peas and a light, creamy sauce. The goal is to create a dish that is both comforting and easy to prepare, with a balance of protein, vegetables, and carbohydrates.",
    "recipe":
        {
            "title": "Creamy Chicken Pasta with Peas",
            "description": "This recipe is a delightful combination of tender chicken pieces, sweet peas, and pasta enveloped in a light creamy sauce. It's a comforting and easy-to-make dish that's perfect for a weeknight dinner.",
            "list_of_steps": [
                {
                    "step": "Gather all the ingredients: boneless chicken breast, pasta of your choice, fresh or frozen peas, garlic, onion, chicken stock, cream, olive oil, salt, and pepper."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Cut the chicken breast into bite-sized pieces and season with salt and pepper."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Heat a couple of tablespoons of olive oil in a large pan over medium-high heat and saut the chicken pieces until they are golden brown and cooked through. Remove the chicken from the pan and set aside."
                },
                {
                    "step": "In the same pan, add a little more olive oil if needed, and saut a finely chopped onion until translucent. Add minced garlic and cook for another minute until fragrant."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Pour in about a cup of chicken stock and bring to a simmer, scraping up any browned bits from the bottom of the pan."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Add the peas to the pan and cook until they are just tender, which will take about 3-4 minutes for fresh peas or 1-2 minutes for frozen peas."
                },
                {
                    "step": "While the peas are cooking, boil the pasta in a separate pot according to the package instructions until al dente. Drain and set aside."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Reduce the heat under the pan with the peas to low and stir in half a cup of cream, letting it warm through without boiling."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Return the cooked chicken to the pan and add the drained pasta. Toss everything together gently, allowing the pasta to absorb the flavors of the sauce."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Season the pasta with additional salt and pepper to taste. If the sauce is too thick, a splash of pasta water or chicken stock can be added to reach the desired consistency."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Serve the creamy chicken pasta with peas hot, garnished with grated Parmesan cheese or fresh herbs if desired."
                }
            ]
        }
}
